      "# New Macro Template title\n\n```\n# Title\n\n## Description\n\n\n## Add Tags\n(n#)\n\n## Difficulty Level\n\n\n## Gitmind tree branch\n\n\n## Body\n\n\n--\n\n# Title [ES]\n\n## Description\n\n\n## Add Tags\n(n#)\n\n## Difficulty Level\n\n\n## Body\n\n```\n\n# Guidelines:\n\n## How to name new branches?\n\n{ACTION}-{macro_name}\n  Actions:\n  [NEW]\n  [CHANGE]\n  [DEACTIVATE]\n\nSince branches are eliminated once merged, we can have several branches with the same name.\nWhen creating a new macro, we generate a new row in this Google Sheet to have the macro ID number (n#):\nhttps://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/126ZUK5NW9bEDjDKfKqyx4aZWU5L-Py3jckzZr742nSc/edit#gid=1385669334\n\n\n## How to name new commits?\n\nWe'll follow the monorepo naming structure:\ncx:{brief description of the changes} \n\n\n## When to merge a PR?\n\nNEW macro: anyone can approve it, except for sensitive cases that Flor must approve.\nCHANGE or DEACTIVATE macro: Flor approval is required.\n\n\n# Summary\n\n## Create new macro\n\n1. Copy the template\n2. Add file > Create new file\n3. Name the file like the macro. It must be lower-case, without empty spaces and must have `.md` extension.\n    1. this_is_an_example.md\n4. Paste the template\n5. Complete each section\n    1. In the Description include recent or relevant tickets\n    2. To create the macro n# ID go to the end of [this](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/126ZUK5NW9bEDjDKfKqyx4aZWU5L-Py3jckzZr742nSc/edit#gid=1385669334) Sheet, add your new macro name in the first empty row and take it's ID\n6. Add optional comments \n7. Add Reviewers (usually other CX members), Assignee (yourself), `customer-support` and `macros-zendesk` labels and click on 'Create pull request’\n\n## Merge\n\n1. `bors merge`\n2. Create both macros in Zendesk [EN] and [ES]\n3. Update [Sheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/126ZUK5NW9bEDjDKfKqyx4aZWU5L-Py3jckzZr742nSc/edit#gid=1385669334): Body and Description\n4. Update Gitmind (see with Susni or Fer)\n",
