      "# Recover wallet with lost RC\n\n## Description\nWe use this macro only if the user wants to recover their wallet, has lost the RC, and they have recovery = RECOVERY_CODE in Retool. We don't use this macro if we see something different in Retool.\n\nPlease note that we can only identify a user with recovery = RECOVERY_CODE if they share their support code or a transaction ID with us. We cannot use their email to search for them.\n\n## Add Tags\nn213\nrecover_wallet_lost_RC\n\n## Difficulty Level\nHard\n\n## Gitmind tree branch\nProblems > Recovery > User wants to Recover wallet > User’s data matches Retool > RC\n\n## Body\nHi there,\n\nThanks for getting in touch.\n\nTo recover your wallet, you'll need your password or Recovery Code.\n\nThe Recovery Code is a randomly-generated code composed of 32 characters. It combines letters and numbers, and it looks like this:\n\nXXXX - XXXX - XXXX - XXXX\nXXXX - XXXX - XXXX - XXXX\n\nMuun asks you to write down the code on a piece of paper and keep it in a safe place.\n\nMuun is a self-custodial wallet, which means that we do not have access to your private keys or the funds in your wallet. This is a security measure to ensure that you, as the owner of the wallet, are in complete control of your funds.\n\t\nRecovering a self-custodial wallet is not a matter of identifying you as the owner of the wallet; it's about having access to the private keys that control your funds. As a result, we can't recover your wallet for you.\n\nLet me know if this helps.\n\nRegards,\n\n--\n\n# Recover wallet with lost RC [ES]\n\n## Description\nWe use this macro only if the user wants to recover their wallet, has lost the RC, and they have recovery = RECOVERY_CODE in Retool. We don't use this macro if we see something different in Retool.\n\nPlease note that we can only identify a user with recovery = RECOVERY_CODE if they share their support code or a transaction ID with us. We cannot use their email to search for them.\n\n## Add Tags\nn213\nrecover_wallet_lost_RC\n\n## Difficulty Level\nHard\n\n## Body\nHola, gracias porescribirnos.\n\nPara recuperar tu monedero, necesitas tu contraseña o Código de recuperación.\n\nEl Código de recuperación es un código generado aleatoriamente compuesto por 32 caracteres. Combina letras y números, y se ve así:\n\nXXXX - XXXX - XXXX - XXXX\nXXXX - XXXX - XXXX - XXXX\n\nMuun te pide que escribas el código en papel y lo guardes en un lugar seguro.\n\nMuun es un monedero de custodia propia, lo que significa que no tenemos acceso a las claves privadas que controlan los fondos de tu monedero. Esta es una medida de seguridad para garantizar que vos, como dueño del monedero, tengas el control total de tus fondos.\n\nRecuperar un monedero de custodia propia no es una cuestión de identificarte como propietario del mismo; se trata de tener acceso a las claves privadas que controlan tus fondos. Por eso, no podemos recuperar tu monedero por vos.\n\nEspero que esto sea de ayuda.\n\nSaludos,\n",
