    content:
      "# Funds not received from Fixed Float\n\n## Description\n\n## Add Tags\ntransaction_not_received\nfixed_float\nn150\n\n## Difficulty Level\n\n## Body\nHello, thanks for reaching out.\n  \nWe've identified a Fixed Float issue where Lightning transactions are marked as successful when they weren't actually made. We've already reported this problem to them several times, and they have been improving it, but it's still happening. Users in this situation have to contact Fixed Float, and it's usually resolved very quickly.  \n  \nThis is probably the case for you, but I'd be happy to check. Could you share with me the Lightning invoice you were trying to pay?  \n  \nIt looks like this:  \n''  \n  \nCheers,\n\n\n--\n\n# Funds not received from Fixed Float [ES]\n\n## Description\n\n## Add Tags\ntransaction_not_received\nfixed_float\nn150\n\n## Difficulty Level\n\n## Body\nHola, gracias por escribirnos.\n  \nTenemos identificado un problema de Fixed Float, donde marcan transacciones de Lightning como satisfactorias cuando en realidad no se hicieron. Ya les reportamos este problema en varias ocasiones, y lo fueron mejorando, pero aún sigue pasando. Los usuarios en esta situación tienen que comunicarse con Fixed Float, y en general se resuelve muy rápido.\n  \nEs probable que este sea tu caso, pero con gusto lo verifico. Podrías pasarme la factura de Lightning que esperabas pagar? \n  \nSe ve así:\n' __ '\n  \nSaludos,\n  \n\n\n--\n\n",
